VS *is* easy.<br>
<br>
If everything works right.<br>
<br>
If something goes critically wrong, it is pretty much unrecoverable.<br>
<br>
VS strat is MT engages at min melee range, builds a small amount of aggro, all other melee engage at max melee range, two or more chanters chain Rune V on the MT to prevent that gawdawful lifetap proc from being effective. clerics cheal rotate, nukers nuke.<br>
<br>
He's dead quick then.<br>
<br>
Bad Things Include: other melee getting too close and falling to his lifetap proc. Because they are unruned, the lifetap proc goes off successfully and VS gains a not inconsiderable amount of life... prolonging the fight, perhaps to unrecoverable length.<br>
<br>
The MT goes down, which usually results in VS fluttering around torching the other melee, clerics and chanters... again because the other people do not have rune on, VS's lifetap proc goes off, and he's back to full almost terrifyingly quickly.<br>
<br>
The simple strategy allows N random people of moderatly high level.. about 24 or so, to bring him down in short order.<br>
<br>
Of course, the number of people required decreases as levels go up and gear quality goes up... more DPS, fewer people. This is why you hear of two group kills of VS, because it's all about the DPS. <p><BR>
